Junction City School District - Northeast Claiborne Charter is with Robby Lowe and Donna McLelland.
September 3 at 4:18 PM ·

JCSD-NECC Important Message Regarding Free School Breakfast/Lunch Forms:

The United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) and the Arkansas Department of Education announced Wednesday, September 3 that all students will be provided free lunch and breakfast until December 31, 2020 as a response to COVID-19. The school needs all parents to complete and return the free lunch forms that were sent home with your students at the beginning of the year so that when USDA’s waiver on paid lunch ends, we can resume our free and reduced lunch program. Also, free and reduced lunch percentages are used to calculate supplemental Federal and State special funding that supports educational programs. We ask all parents to complete forms and return them as soon as possible. We do not know if the waiver will be extended to include the second semester.

El Dorado-Union County Chamber of Commerce is with Michaela Singleton.
September 2 at 10:52 AM ·

🍎✏️ Because of the current guidelines in place by the CDC, we are having to be creative with how we can show appreciation to our new teachers in Union County this year! Instead of having our annual "New Teachers Breakfast" event, the El Dorado-Union County Chamber of Commerce is visiting local schools individually to show appreciation by providing breakfast and appreciation bags to the new teachers!

Our first "New Teachers Breakfast" event was yesterday in Junction City, where we welcomed their new teachers! Thank you Junction City School District teachers! We hope you have a fantastic year!!

National Online Safety has put together some fantastic resources for parents about social media apps, online games, and trending issues so they can have informed discussions with their children. THESE ARE PICTURES OF THE DOCUMENTS to give you an idea of what's available/discussed.

All resources, plus much more, can be accessed from the National Online Safety website: https://nationalonlinesafety.com/resources/wake-up-wednesday/
You can register for free and get a weekly update.

You can download some of the resources from a Google Drive folder: http://bit.ly/2v8rsEX (additional resources available from National Online Safety website, )

Visit the National Online Safety Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/NationalOnlineSafety/

post_text: Thanks to an awesome JCES parent's idea AMANDA HAWKINS, we have created a JCSD wish list on Amazon.com for our ongoing Backpack Food Drive! This is just a wish list only so you will be able to choose the brand, quantity and kind of food you wish to donate. If you would like to use this option, the food will be sent directly to the school's address in care of our nurse Michelle Faulkner Doolin! When you are in your Amazon account, you must add our wishlist so JCSD Backpack Food Drive Wish List will show up on your Amazon page. #DragonsFeedingDragons

CDC
November 18, 2019 at 11:00 AM ·

It’s U.S. Antibiotic Awareness Week! Antibiotics save lives and are critical tools for treating infections, like those that can lead to sepsis. When antibiotics aren’t needed – like for a cold – they won’t help you, and their side effects could cause harm. Serious side effects can include C. difficile infection, which can cause deadly diarrhea. Talk to your doctor about the best way to treat your illness. http://bit.ly/2AEuUHV
